The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for MRI image reconstruction, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). It also focuses on compressive sensing (CS) and signal recovery, which are key areas in information theory (cs.IT). The use of deep neural networks (DNNs) for image reconstruction also falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of state-of-the-art image denoising techniques, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of iterative algorithms for image reconstruction, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
